commit.message:
Fixed ivy-rich-modify-column (#107)

The issue is, the columns props are not updated due to the plist-put
call is not set back to `ivy-rich-display-transformers-list`.

If any column is modified, we also need to rebuild the transformer
function. But we don't do backup. We should ONLY backup transformers
before enabling `ivy-rich`, not the ones before modified after when
`ivy-rich` is enabled.

commit.message: Minor formatting, rename cache to ivy-rich--project-root-cache

Introduced ivy-rich-project-root-cache-mode (#93)

While the global ivy-rich-project-root-cache-mode minor mode is enabled, the
results of ivy-rich-switch-buffer-root are cached in a hash-table and evicted
once the buffer is killed or the minor mode is disabled again.

Add convenience functions for customizing transformer columns (#96)

* Add convenience functions for customizing transformer columns

This enables customization of a column properties without rewriting the entire
transformer definition. Two functions are defined; the latter is a wrapper
around the former:

- ivy-rich-modify-column
- ivy-rich-modify-columns

Closes Yevgnen/ivy-rich#95

* Use org-mode syntax for inline code in README

Co-authored-by: Jeff Valk <jeff.valk@admetsys.com>

commit.message:
Make buffer directory only show where relevant (#92)

* Make buffer directory only show where relevant

Previously, directories would be shown for file-less buffers like *scratch*
or *Messages*. This change make sure that directories are only shown for
buffers that actuall have one, for example dired, magit, and buffers visiting
real files.

* Fine-tune comment re list-buffers-directory

commit.message:
Various packaging fixes (#85)

- The code requires Emacs 25.1, so update declared dependency
- Use `_` prefix for unused lexical args to make byte compiler happy
- Require certain libraries at compilation time to satisfy byte compiler
- Don't escape `/` in regexes: it is not a special char (see `relint` package)
- Be explicit about tabs vs spaces
- Add missing standard keyword, and add a Homepage header
- Don't use the deprecated `cl` alias `remove-if`: prefer `cl-remove-if` from `cl-lib`

- The code requires Emacs 25.1, so update declared dependency
